import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='year', y='wheat', data=data)
    chart.set_title('What is the trend of wheat production over the years?', wrap=True)
    return chart

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna()
    data['year'] = data['year'].dt.year
    chart = sns.barplot(x='year', y='wages', data=data, color='blue')
    chart.axhline(y=data['wages'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Average Wage')
    chart.legend(loc='upper left')
    plt.title('What is the average wage per year?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    plt.title('What is the correlation between wheat production and wages?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['wheat'] = pd.to_numeric(data['wheat'], errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='wheat', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['wheat'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of wheat production?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['wages'] = pd.to_numeric(data['wages'], errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='wages', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['wages'].median(), color='red', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['wages'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of wages?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
